name: iShares Semiconductor Index ETF
longDescription: The ETF currently seeks to replicate the performance of the ICE Semiconductor Index (the Index). The Index measures the performance of the equity securities of the 30 largest U.S.-listed companies that are classified according to the ICE Uniform Sector Classification schema within the semiconductors industry. The ETF will primarily invest in U.S. equity securities and/or securities of one or more ETFs managed by BlackRock or an affiliate. The ETF seeks to provide longterm capital growth by replicating, to the extent possible, the performance, net of expenses, of an Index selected at the discretion of BlackRock that is composed of U.S.listed securities of issuers classified as being within the semiconductors industry, as determined by the index provider.
